# Proper server-side 301s (Cloudflare) — replaces Astro's static meta-refresh
# pages so social scrapers and search engines follow them. Destinations carry
# the trailing slash to match the canonical URLs (avoids an extra hop).
# Format rename (Jul 2026): beats → play, reads → read, dashboards → explore.
# Splats carry deep links (old shared article/deck/dashboard URLs) across.
# /economy points straight at the read shelf — never chain through /reads.
# The old beats page IS the payments deck, so its index goes to the deck's
# permanent URL (alive but unlisted since decks left the rack) — sending an
# old share to the rack would swap the cards someone was promised for a game.
/economy/beats/*        /economy/play/:splat     301
/economy/beats          /economy/play/payments/  301
/economy/beats/         /economy/play/payments/  301
/economy/reads/*        /economy/read/:splat     301
/economy/reads          /economy/read/           301
/economy/reads/         /economy/read/           301
# Desks fold (Jul 2026): the six standalone dashboards live on as desks of
# /economy/explore/payments/. Explicit lines sit above the /dashboards/*
# splat so first-match-wins sends old deep links there in one hop.
/economy/dashboards/overview          /economy/explore/payments/  301
/economy/dashboards/product-view      /economy/explore/payments/  301
/economy/dashboards/bank-performance  /economy/explore/payments/  301
/economy/dashboards/upi-ecosystem     /economy/explore/payments/  301
